nity Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: I think I will...</span><hr size=1> were you a caster or a ranger before the warrior ?<br>just curious.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usumarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sumarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 1:09:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1746.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  ?</span><hr size=1> Why do you ask?<br><br>People seem to be shocked if I worry about the damage I am dealing... I understand warriors are great punching bags and need aggro more than anything and I am very fond of snagging aggro and being beat into a bloody pulp. I am first and foremost a aggro/ac monkey, but it doesn't hurt to dish damage also.<br><br>I have seen this rather large argument on various message boards about if a Frosty is too slow for primary or is the greatest thing since sliced bread. I'm not sure where I stand on this issue which is why I posted here. Does speed necessarily mean better aggro in all cases? If this is the case then I should dig up a Jade mace post haste even though the damage on it is terrible for my level. Yes, at 58+ its uber damage, at 38 it kinda sucks compared to other weapons with better ratio such as Frostbringer.<br><br>In any case, if your question was prompted by my lack of love for the overpriced Defiance, it has a lot to do with the fact that my bagged lammy could do the same thing dam/delay wise and I do not want to spend a lot of money on a bit of ac that I already have with my current setup. It is not that Defiance sucks as a weapon, it just sucks for me. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>If speed is all that matters then I will probably snag a Jade mace for the admittedly very nice 18 delay. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushikariiapoccalypse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shikarii Apoccalypse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Steel Warrior Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 994<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 1:38:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1746.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: ?</span><hr size=1> you apply everything in theory about 5% this and +10 that and -5 them and increaseXlevel/sta^phase of the moon math.<br><br>sure, it's great to try to look into things with some research first; but; staring down through the microscope at every detail is kinda . . . . just too much analysis.<br><br>i mean in all honesty, pre-45 the Wurmslayer is balls-out damage case closed vs anything you could possibly wield.<br>offhanded the delay on the Frostbringer is awesome due to it's ratio. primary handed it's a tad slow i agree; but increasing speed on your primary hand weapon will give you more damage per minute, or even attempted damage per inute for arguements sake and generate aggro.<br><br>lammy is a great weapon. i use it ofen due to my lack of stamina base.<br>would i take the lammy over the venemous axe ? yup. overall primary handed the lamentation is a great performing weapon. so what if random_twink1.0eX100 all have 2 of them ? the weapon works great.<br><br>and since you have a frosty, the offhand potenial is devastating. you can wield that puppy damn near to 60 and not complain. now it's a bit slow due to not having your DW skill high enough yet, but in time you will and not grow out of it.<br><br>than, taking the lammy, and, replacing it with:<br>a. Defiance<br>b. Wavecrasher<br><br>you don't lose aggro generated, and, gain either AC or a proc which is a great aggro generator.<br><br>sheesh, now i've gone off and rambled : it just seemed odd you were asking for advice where you already had your questions answered in your own head.<br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>but that's my 2 bits. <p><center><img src=http://publish.hometown.aol.com/crushr85/myhomepage/shir_small.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usumarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sumarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 2:28:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1746.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  oh :)</span><hr size=1> Oh, lol, I'm sorry I thought your question about a previous class was a pre-flame flame... no, I tend to evaluate things like dam/delay ratio, dps and crap like that because I am a programmer, and I'm bored at work. It gives me a great deal of extra time to sit and think about the best weapon combo for when I actually sit down and play. I tend to be fairly analytical anyway and being a programmer its even worse. <br><br>Besides, am I the only person that thinks the intricate weapon/combat system is awesome? I love that there is Everquest MATH for weapons...Ruatha would understand <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I am going to play around with my Lammy/FB I guess and see how that works for me. Besides I think the playing field is going to change a bit once the Frosty starts proccing.<br><br>As far as answering my own question...no I still haven't had it answered satisfactorily to be honest. ..*sigh* It would help if some people who are higher level and use the frostbringer in primary could relate experiences, or even people who have -tried- to use FB in prim and didn't feel it worked well.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 287<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 3:32:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1746.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Weapon selection...</span><hr size=1> My warrior just dinged 46 last night so I am not too far ahead of you mainhand bonus wise. Since 40 here are the combos I have tried:<br><br>Jarsath Trident (11/22)/Velium warsword (10/24)<br>Lammy (9/19)/ JT<br>Lammy/Lammy<br>Jade Mace (9/1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> /Lammy<br>Frostbringer (12/22)/JT<br>Defiance (9/19)/FB<br><br>For all out damage the FB/JT combo did the most damage but I was dependent on the proc to keep agro. If the FB didn't proc a couple times I found I was having a hard time keeping agro. I actually could hold agro more reliably with dual lammys or JM/lammy than with FB mainhand.<br><br>A couple of days ago I got my hands on a Defiance and moved the FB to offhand. The FB still procs a lot offhand but the added speed from the Defiance made a world of difference. Last night in ME I was pulling agro off of a 60 Pali and a 2hs weilding 56 war if they didn't pay attention and keep after the mob or when the Pali would go oom. When they left, I could reliably hold agro with a 52 Pali (not using stuns, I had more HP) and a 56 Bard.<br><br>It has been my experience that faster weapons offer much more taunt, even if they are hitting for much lower. I often hunt with another 46 warrior that weilds Wurmy/Centi LS with an FBSS. I can practically keep the mob glue to me even without hitting the taunt button even though his combo FAR outdamages mine.<br><br>This is the way I see it. A mob remembers a big hit longer, but if you keep on swatching at it over and over it will have a hard time forgetting all the small hits in between the big blasts. If damage &gt; speed for taunt then everyone would be using 2h weapons to MT. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial"><img src="http://www.bfdesigns.net/eq/wandor_sig.jpg"><br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor's profile</b></a> | <a target="_blank" href="http://www.exarch.net/"><b>Fusion of Flame</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102" target="_blank"><b>Moordian's profile</b></a></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usumarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sumarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 5:07:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1746.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  yup</span><hr size=1> Yeah, I am definitely getting the same feeling in my own aggro world... although I could &quot;mostly&quot; keep taunt off my friends 47 rogue in exp grind...my other 37 warr friend using lammy/lsoee was taunting off me pretty badly. I think the 3 delay drop from the Frosty to Lammy in main hand means a whole lot. <br><br>The real question then is...how much does 1 delay matter? As I already have a lammy, I'm somewhat loathe to swap lammy for a jade mace, losing 6 str/stam 20 hps for 1 delay. Eek. <br><br>I think I will probably just Lammy/FB until I can get a Wavecrasher. I really really want a WC. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  When does the 'Crasher proc btw? Also, anybody on Xegony wanna sell one for rl cash? :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uswanda08.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swanda08</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 6:07:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1746.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title